<HEAD>$Adv09</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Sunday, July 9, and Thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>Capsules of 12 Who Walked on Moon</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Part of an eight-story package for use at will or on successful
Sundays in July.</HEAD>
<HEAD>With LaserPhoto</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By HOWARD BENEDICT</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Aerospace Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Twelve men, all Americans, walked on
the moon in those heady days of Apollo exploration. Their fame was
fleeting and their names today are mostly dim memories.
   <PERSON>Neil Armstrong</PERSON> earned a place in history 20 years ago when he
became the first human to leave his footprints in the ancient lunar
dust.
   The rest, in order: <PERSON>Buzz Aldrin</PERSON>, <PERSON>Charles Conrad Jr.</PERSON>, <PERSON>Alan L.
Bean</PERSON>, <PERSON>Alan B. Shepard Jr.</PERSON>, <PERSON>Edgar D. Mitchell</PERSON>, <PERSON>David R. Scott</PERSON>, <PERSON>James
B. Irwin</PERSON>, <PERSON>John W. Young</PERSON>, <PERSON>Charles M. Duke Jr.</PERSON>, <PERSON>Eugene A. Cernan</PERSON> and
<PERSON>Harrison H. Schmitt</PERSON>.
   Each was affected profoundly by his stay on the moon and the
perspective it gave them of <LOCATION>Earth</LOCATION>.
   ``My impression was of the importance of that small, fragile,
remote blue planet,'' <ORGANIZATION>Armstrong</ORGANIZATION> reported. ``People everywhere have,
by television and photographs, shared that perspective and shared
our concern for the security of our globe.''
   Nine of the moon-walkers are business executives, one is an
artist, one is an evangelist, and one remains with <ORGANIZATION>NASA</ORGANIZATION>, an
engineering trouble-shooter.
   Here is a glance:
   _ <PERSON>Neil A. Armstrong</PERSON>, 58 ... aeronautical engineering degree from
Purdue ... flew 78 combat missions in <LOCATION>Korea</LOCATION> ... X-15 test pilot ...
commanded Gemini 8, aborted shortly after the first docking of two
vehicles in space ... first man to walk on the moon ... shunned the
spotlight and became a professor of aerospace engineering at the
<ORGANIZATION>University of Cincinnati</ORGANIZATION> for nine years ... chairman <ORGANIZATION>CTA Inc.</ORGANIZATION>,
<LOCATION>Lebanon</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Ohio</LOCATION>, a computer systems company.
   _ <PERSON>Buzz Aldrin</PERSON>, 59 ... born <PERSON>Edwin E. Aldrin Jr.</PERSON>, but legally
changed name ... son of a general ... West Point honor graduate ...
fighter pilot in <LOCATION>Korea</LOCATION> ... Gemini 12 space walker ... landed on the
moon with <ORGANIZATION>Armstrong</ORGANIZATION> on Apollo 11 ... commander of the <ORGANIZATION>Aerospace
Research Pilots School</ORGANIZATION> ... passed over for promotion to brigadier
general by the <ORGANIZATION>Air Force</ORGANIZATION> ... suffered mental depression and bouts
with alcoholism and recovered from both ... now president of his own
Los Angeles-based firm, <ORGANIZATION>Research &amp; Engineering Consultants</ORGANIZATION>.
   _ <PERSON>Charles Conrad Jr.</PERSON>, 59 ... engineering degree from <LOCATION>Princeton</LOCATION>
... <ORGANIZATION>Navy</ORGANIZATION> test pilot ... eight days in space aboard Gemini 5 ...
commanded Gemini 11 ... commanded Apollo 12 moon landing ... daring
space walks helped save crippled Skylab station ... now a senior
vice president of <ORGANIZATION>Douglas Aircraft Co.</ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION>Long Beach</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Calif</LOCATION>.
   _ <PERSON>Alan L. Bean</PERSON>, 57 ... aeronautical engineering degree from
<ORGANIZATION>University of Texas ... Navy</ORGANIZATION> test pilot ... holder of 11 world
records in space and aeronautics ... landed on the moon with Conrad
... commanded 56-day Skylab 2 flight ... resigned from <ORGANIZATION>NASA</ORGANIZATION> in <DATE>1981</DATE>
to devote time to his hobby, painting, and now turns out expensive
canvases of the moon and other space scenes in his <LOCATION>Houston</LOCATION> studio.
   _ <PERSON>Alan B. Shepard Jr.</PERSON>, 65 ... <ORGANIZATION>Naval Academy</ORGANIZATION> graduate ... carrier
and test pilot ... only one of the seven original Mercury astronauts
to walk on the moon ... first American in space, a 15-minute
suborbital flight in <DATE>1961</DATE> ... grounded for several years by an ear
disorder ... commanded Apollo 14 moon landing ... several banking,
real estate and other business interests have made him a <LOCATION>Houston</LOCATION>
millionaire.
   _ <PERSON>Edgar D. Mitchell</PERSON>, 58 ... doctorate of science from MIT ...
<ORGANIZATION>Navy</ORGANIZATION> carrier and test pilot ... landed on the moon with <PERSON>Shepard</PERSON> ...
en route to moon he conducted extrasensory perception experiments
with a friend in <LOCATION>Chicago</LOCATION> ... on return he concentrated on research
into psychic phenomena and wrote a book about it ... now chairman of
<ORGANIZATION>Forecast Systems Inc.</ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION>West Palm Beach</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Fla</LOCATION>.
   _ <PERSON>David R. Scott</PERSON>, 57 ... fifth in <LOCATION>West Point</LOCATION> class ... master of
science from <ORGANIZATION>MIT ... Air Force</ORGANIZATION> test pilot ... flew with <ORGANIZATION>Armstrong</ORGANIZATION> on
the aborted Gemini 8 flight ... commander of Apollo 9 Earth-orbiting
mission that tested the Lunar Module ... commanded Apollo 15 moon
landing ... <PERSON>Scott</PERSON> and crewmates <PERSON>James B. Irwin</PERSON> and <PERSON>Alfred P. Worden</PERSON>
admitted carrying 400 unauthorized stamps to the moon which they
planned to sell; all three were removed from astronaut status ...
<PERSON>Scott</PERSON> became director of <ORGANIZATION>NASA</ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION>Flight Research School</ORGANIZATION> and now is
president of <ORGANIZATION>Scott Science and Technology</ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION>Lancaster</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Calif</LOCATION>.
   _ <PERSON>James B. Irwin</PERSON>, 59 ... <ORGANIZATION>Naval Academy</ORGANIZATION> graduate ... <ORGANIZATION>Air Force</ORGANIZATION>
test pilot ... with <PERSON>Scott</PERSON>, drove first lunar car on the moon ...
viewed his Apollo 15 moon journey as an overwhelming religious
experience ... founded High Flight, an interdenominational
evangelistic foundation, headquartered in <LOCATION>Colorado Springs</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Colo.</LOCATION>
... slowed by three heart attacks, but continues his religious work
... made six expeditions to Mount Ararat in <LOCATION>Turkey</LOCATION> in search for
<ORGANIZATION>Noah</ORGANIZATION>'s ark.
   _ <PERSON>John W. Young</PERSON>, 58 ... aeronautical engineering graduate of
<ORGANIZATION>Georgia Tech</ORGANIZATION> ... piloted Gemini 3, the first manned <ORGANIZATION>Gemini</ORGANIZATION> flight,
and commanded Gemini 10 ... orbited moon on Apollo 10 and landed as
commander of Apollo 16 ... only moonwalker to fly on the space
shuttle, commanding the first and ninth missions ... has made a
record six space flights ... served as chief of the astronaut office
and now is special assistant for engineering operations and safety
at <ORGANIZATION>NASA</ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION>Johnson Space Center</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>Houston</LOCATION>.
   _ <PERSON>Charles M. Duke Jr.</PERSON>, 53 ... <ORGANIZATION>Naval Academy</ORGANIZATION> graduate ... master
of science from <ORGANIZATION>MIT ... Air Force</ORGANIZATION> test pilot ... landed on the moon
with Young ... now a partner in <ORGANIZATION>Duke Investments</ORGANIZATION> and president of
<ORGANIZATION>Southwest Wilderness Art</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>San Antonio</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Texas</LOCATION>.
   _ <PERSON>Eugene A. Cernan</PERSON>, 55 ... degree in electrical engineering from
<LOCATION>Purdue</LOCATION> ... <ORGANIZATION>Navy</ORGANIZATION> fighter pilot ... Gemini 9 spacewalker ... flew
within 10 miles of the moon on Apollo 10 ... commanded Apollo 17,
last Apollo moon-landing mission ... helped plan <DATE>1975</DATE> U.S.-Soviet
manned flight ... now president of the <ORGANIZATION>Houston-based Cernan
Corporation</ORGANIZATION>, which consults on aerospace, energy and related
industries.
   _ <PERSON>Harrison H. Schmitt</PERSON>, 54 ... doctorate in geology from <LOCATION>Harvard</LOCATION>
... served with <ORGANIZATION>U.S. Geological Survey</ORGANIZATION>'s Astrogeology Branch ...
trained astronauts in geology before joining the corps ... first
geologist on the moon, on Apollo 17 ... served one term as <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION>
senator from <LOCATION>New Mexico</LOCATION> ... now a business consultant in <LOCATION>Albuquerque</LOCATION>.
</TEXT>
