<FIRST>u a PM-Apollo-20YearsAgo     07-17 0147</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Apollo-20 Years Ago,0148</SECOND>
<HEAD>What Happened 20 Years Ago On Historic Flight</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Apollo Anniversary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are highlights of what occurred
exactly <DATE>20 years ago today</DATE> during the Apollo 11 moon flight:
   One day after launch, Apollo 11 is streaking outward from <LOCATION>Earth</LOCATION>
toward the moon, which is still more than 100,000 miles ahead.
   At <TIME>12:17 p.m. EDT</TIME>, the astronauts fire the rocket engine on
<ORGANIZATION>Columbia</ORGANIZATION>, their command and service module, for three seconds, just
long enough to put the craft precisely on target for the moon.
   Later, astronauts <PERSON>Neil Armstrong</PERSON>, <PERSON>Edwin E.</PERSON> ``Buzz'' <PERSON>Aldrin Jr.</PERSON>
and <PERSON>Michael Collins</PERSON> beam a 36-minute television show to <ORGANIZATION>Mission
Control</ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION>Houston</LOCATION>. They show a view of the <LOCATION>Earth</LOCATION>, now 128,000 miles
behind them, and then give a tour of their small space cabin.
   At <TIME>9:42 p.m. EDT</TIME>, <ORGANIZATION>Mission Control</ORGANIZATION> bids the crew goodnight.
</TEXT>
